{{Infobox artwork | title = History Painting | image_file = Rembrandt Historical Painting 1626.jpg | artist = [[Rembrandt]] | catalogue = | year = {{start date|1626}} | material = oil on panel | subject = | height_metric = 90 | width_metric = 122 | metric_unit = cm<!--don't leave blank—either don't include it, or include the default cm. --> | imperial_unit = in<!--don't leave blank—either don't include it, or include the default in. --> }}
'''''History Painting''''' is an early painting by [[Rembrandt]] dating to 1626. The title is a generic reference to [[history painting]], as there is no consensus about the painting's subject matter. More than a dozen subjects have been proposed, ranging from Biblical themes to classical and modern history.<ref>{{Cite book |author=van de Wetering, Ernst |title=A Corpus of Rembrandt Paintings |date=2015 |publisher=Springer |isbn=9789401791731}}</ref>
Owned by the Instituut Collectie Nederland, it is on permanent loan to the [[Stedelijk Museum De Lakenhal]] in [[Leiden]].<ref name="RijnWetering2006">{{cite book|author1=Rembrandt Harmenszoon van Rijn|author2=Ernst van de Wetering|author3=Michiel Franken |author4=Museum Het Rembrandthuis |author5=Gemäldegalerie |title=Rembrandt, quest of a genius|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ShjrAAAAMAAJ|accessdate=9 September 2013|year=2006|publisher=Waanders Publishers|isbn=978-90-400-8167-5}}</ref>
