[[File:The Office gallery.jpg|alt=The Office gallery facade.|thumb|The Office gallery facade.]] '''The Office''' is a contemporary art gallery located in the centre of the old town<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/travel/article/can-art-reunite-divided-capital/index.html|title=Can cultural revival heal rift in Cyprus' divided capital? {{!}} CNN Travel|date=2013-12-17|work=CNN Travel|access-date=2017-10-13|language=en}}</ref> of [[Nicosia]] in [[Cyprus]] near the boundaries of the [[United Nations Buffer Zone in Cyprus|Green Line]], which makes Nicosia the last divided capital in [[European Union|Europe]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = Nicosia: the last divided capital in the world|url = http://www.cnn.com/2013/12/16/travel/gallery/nicosia-the-last-divided-capital-in-the-world/index.html|website = CNN|access-date = 21 January 2016|date = 17 December 2013}}</ref> The location is a stimulus for some artists who have exhibited their work in the Office gallery.<ref>{{Cite web|title = The punk Robert Burns of the contemporary art world|url = http://www.dazeddigital.com/artsandculture/article/21361/1/the-punk-robert-burns-of-the-contemporary-art-world|website = Dazed|access-date = 21 January 2016|date = 2015|last = Cobb|first = Ben}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Μια εικαστική "Οδός Ελευθερίας" στην Πράσινη Γραμμή|url = http://www.tovima.gr/culture/article/?aid=461045|website = TO BHMA|access-date = 21 January 2016|date = 6 June 2012}}</ref> It was founded in 2009 by the Greek Anastasios Gkekas.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Anastasios Gkekas brings 'Investment Opportunities' to VOLKS gallery, Cyprus|url = http://www.wallpaper.com/art/anastasios-gkekas-brings-investment-opportunities-to-volks-gallery-cyprus#ZKHpKHlmcl6DVbge.99|website = Wallpaper*|access-date = 21 January 2016|first = Siska|last = Lyssens|date = 16 September 2015}}</ref> To date the gallery has mounted 20 exhibitions by both European and non-European artists. In 2015 and 2016 the gallery, along with solo shows, mounted two group shows with works by local and international artists. The 2015 show titled "Investment Opportunities" consisted solely of works from the gallery's collection,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://anti-utopias.com/newswire/investment-opportunities/|title=Investment Opportunities.|last=Bors|first=Sabin|date=October 27, 2015|website=anti-utopias|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref> and the 2016 show "To Express the Feelings of a Chair When We Sit on it" included works that were loaned for the purposes of this exhibition, accompanied by pieces from the gallery's collection.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://independent-collectors.com/exhibitions/t-a-gkekas-to-express-the-feelings-of-a-chair-when-we-sit-on-it|title=THE OFFICE – TO EXPRESS THE FEELINGS OF A CHAIR WHEN WE SIT ON IT|website=Independent Collectors|publisher=Independent Collectors|access-date=11 November 2016}}</ref> __FORCETOC__ == Art Brussels == In 2015, the Office gallery participated in the Art Brussels 2015 international art fair, presenting works by the Scottish artist [[Robert Montgomery (artist)|Robert Montgomery]] and the Greek artist Dimitris Merantzas, entitled “Proof against the obtainment of new artwork”.<ref>{{Cite web|title = SOME/ART : THE OFFICE GALLERY AT ART BRUSSELS 2015|url = http://www.someslashthings.com/online-magazine/2015/5/2/someart-the-office-gallery-at-art-brussels-2015|website = SOME/THINGS|access-date = 21 January 2015|date = 2 May 2015}}</ref>
